body.description: Deliver premium quality to your baby with Huggies Special Delivery Baby Diapers. Special Delivery Baby Diapers are our Softest Diapers Guaranteed*, love it or we'll refund it 100%! Dermatologist-tested and clinically proven to be hypoallergenic, these disposable baby diapers are made with plant-based materials** (**20%+ by weight) for trusted performance. Special Delivery offers Huggies Trusted Protection with responsibly-sourced materials.*** Not only are these super soft diapers safe for sensitive skin, but they also do not contain harsh ingredients and are free of fragrances, lotions, parabens, and elemental chlorine bleach. These baby diapers are crafted with a contoured shape, soft flexible leg cuffs and a back pocketed waistband to help prevent diaper blowouts and contain the mess. They absorb wetness and lock away moisture to keep your baby's skin clean and healthy, while a 100% breathable outer cover ensures airflow. Plus, with a wetness indicator, you'll always know when your little one is ready for a diaper change! Huggies Special Delivery Diapers feature adorable 101 Dalmatians designs and are available in size Newborn (up to 10 lbs), size 1 (up to 14 lbs), size 2 (12-18 lbs), size 3 (16-28 lbs), size 4 (22-37 lbs), size 5 (27+ lbs), and size 6 (35+ lbs). They’re made with plant-based materials*, dermatologist tested, clinically proven hypoallergenic, and backed by our trusted leakage protection. *20% by weight Do Huggies Special Delivery Baby Diapers have fragrance? reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Premium Comfort for Newborns: Huggies Special Delivery Diapers
reviews.reviewText: Huggies Special Delivery Hypoallergenic Baby Diapers in size Newborn have been an absolute game-changer for us. These diapers provide premium comfort and protection for our little one, giving us confidence in their well-being.The hypoallergenic feature is a standout benefit. Knowing that these diapers are designed with sensitive skin in mind provides us with peace of mind. Our baby has experienced no irritation or discomfort since we started using them.The fit is exceptional. The size Newborn is perfect for our little one, ensuring a snug and secure fit that prevents any leaks or accidents. The elastic waistband and leg cuffs provide a comfortable seal without being too tight.The absorbency of these diapers is impressive. They handle wetness effectively, keeping our baby dry and comfortable for extended periods. This is particularly crucial during the night, as it allows for uninterrupted sleep for both baby and parents.We also appreciate the thoughtful design elements, such as the wetness indicator that changes color when it's time for a diaper change. It's a handy feature that eliminates the guesswork.The materials used in these diapers feel soft and gentle against our baby's skin. It's evident that Huggies has put a lot of care into creating a diaper that prioritizes comfort and well-being.Overall, Huggies Special Delivery Hypoallergenic Baby Diapers in size Newborn have become our go-to choice for diapers. They offer premium comfort, excellent fit, and reliable absorbency. Knowing that they are hypoallergenic gives us confidence in their safety for our little one's sensitive skin. We highly recommend these diapers to other parents looking for a high-quality and reliable diaper option. They deserve a resounding five-star rating!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best diaper on the market
reviews.reviewText: You can trust this mother of three children that this is hands-down, the best diaper out there. Say goodbye to blowouts because this product is super absorbent, soft, yet breathable, and the material is thick compared to any other brand out there. Plus the designs on the diapers are super cute! I’m currently on a subscription plan for the diapers, which helps save some money also. You will not regret trying this!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I have been using these for months and they are truly the best. They hold up, and for a plus super soft on her skin. And they are really cute with the Dalmatian designs. They are a bit pricey but they work. I’d rather have that than cheap ones I would have to buy over and over again because they won’t last. I definitely recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Gentle Care for Your Little One: Huggies Special Delivery Hypoallergenic Baby Diapers Review
reviews.reviewText: I recently started using Huggies Special Delivery Hypoallergenic Baby Diapers Size 4 for my little one, and I am incredibly happy with my choice. These fragrance-free, hypoallergenic diapers are specifically designed for sensitive skin, ensuring the utmost care and comfort for my baby.The soft, plant-based materials used in these diapers are not only gentle on my baby's skin but also environmentally friendly. The diapers provide excellent absorbency, keeping my baby dry and comfortable throughout the day and night.I appreciate the secure fit of Huggies Special Delivery diapers, with their flexible waistband and stretchy side panels that adapt to my baby's movements. This ensures a snug and comfortable fit, preventing leaks and ensuring my baby's comfort.The wetness indicator on the diaper is a helpful feature, allowing me to know when it's time for a diaper change without any guesswork. Additionally, the diapers are free from harmful chemicals, fragrances, and latex, making them safe for my baby's delicate skin.In conclusion, Huggies Special Delivery Hypoallergenic Baby Diapers Size 4 have been a fantastic choice for my little one with sensitive skin. The soft, plant-based materials, excellent absorbency, and secure fit ensure my baby stays comfortable and dry all day long. I highly recommend these diapers to any parent seeking gentle and effective care for their baby.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars “Happy babies are Huggies babies!”
reviews.reviewText: I purchased the size 5 (120count) from Amazon, because it’s difficult to find this count in store, but I have always been a huge Special Delivery Huggies fan! I have tried various of other diapers from all price ranges, but I always go back to these. The only other Huggies diaper that compares is the overnight ones. Both are equally as good! So soft, no rashes, and no blowouts if you opened them as you should.Not too thin or thick. My daughter has used these since she was born, and she’s 13months now. I will definitely be sticking to Huggies until she’s out of diapers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This was a baby shower gift sent 3k miles in anticipation of my newest nephew's arrival. I had heard from the Grand Pa to be that "newborn" size diapers are very hard to find in stores. I always loved Huggies when my son was born. They were absorbent and fit very well. Moms know how important those features are! I am sure that today they are an even better product. My gift was very appreciated.
Mi bebé los disfruta y nosotros como papás también , es mucho mejor que cualquier Huggies del mercado . Absorbe y aguanta toda la noche
For having a sensitive baby these diapers are amazing and have such cute patterns !

I feel like the quality of these diapers has gone downhill in the last year. They tear easily, the material inside is poorly distributed for absorbency (as other reviewers have noted), and worst of all, we have thrown out approximately 10% of these diapers because the gel balls that absorb liquid are falling out. If you shake a diaper, they just spill out or sometimes our baby would end up with hundreds of these all around his groin area and inside the belly button. One time, the belly button even got infected. We are not going to buy any more of these again. For the price, no longer worth it. They need to do something about the manufacturing and quality control process.

Lovely and soft for little babies. Switched to a different brand for about a year and a half then went back to these when AZ ran out of stock on the other. The first time we tried them was overnight and she leaked for the first time ever. Fluke? No. They can’t hold even one toddler pee. And we change after every pee so we can say that they literally fall off and/or the sides rip apart every time, after only one pee. Never mind anything else! Honestly considering just tossing the rest of the box.
